 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Adjustments to total income. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Operating subsidy will reflect changes in inflation, utility rates and consumption, and changes in the number
of units in the project.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) In addition to the amount of income derived from the project (from sources such as rents and charges) and the operating
subsidy calculated in accordance with paragraph (a) of this section, the contract may specify that income be provided
to the project from other sources of income of the HA.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The following conditions may not affect the amounts to be provided to a project managed by a resident management
corporation under this subpart:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Any reduction in the total income of a HA that occurs as a result of fraud, waste, or mismanagement by the HA; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Any change in the total income of a HA that occurs as a result of project-specific characteristics that are not
shared by the project managed by the corporation under this subpart.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Retention of excess revenues. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Any income generated by a resident management corporation that exceeds the income estimated for the income category
involved must be excluded in subsequent years in calculating: (1) The operating subsidy provided to a HA under subpart
J of this part; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The funds provided by the HA to the resident management corporation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Use of retained revenues. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Any revenues retained by a resident management corporation under paragraph (d) of this section may only be used for
purposes of improving the maintenance and operation of the project, establishing business enterprises that employ
residents of Indian housing, or acquiring additional dwelling units for low-income families. Units acquired by
the resident management corporation will not be eligible for payment of operating subsidy.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;905.972 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
TOP Audit and administrative requirements.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Annual audit of books and records. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The financial statements of a RMC managing a project under this subpart must be audited annually by a licensed certified
public accountant, designated by the RMC, in accordance with generally accepted government audit standards. A written
report of each audit must be forwarded to HUD and the HA within 30 days of issuance.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Relationship to other authorities. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The requirements of paragraph (a) of this section are in addition to any other Federal law or other requirement that
would apply to the availability and audit of books and records of RMCs under this part.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General administrative requirements. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Except as modified by this part, RMCs must comply with the requirements of OMB Circulars A&hyph;110 and A&hyph;122,
as applicable.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
Family Investment Centers (FIC) Program
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;905.980 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
General.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The Family Investment Centers (FIC) Program. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This program provides families living in Indian housing with better access to educational and employment opportunities
by:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) developing facilities in or near Indian housing for training and support services;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) mobilizing public and private resources to expand and improve the delivery of such services;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) providing funding for such essential training and support services that cannot otherwise be funded; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) improving the capacity of management to assess the training and service needs of families, coordinating the provision
of training and services that meet such needs, and ensuring the long-term provision of such training and services.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Supportive Services. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
New or significantly expanded services essential to providing families in Indian housing with better access to educational
and employment opportunities to achieve self-sufficiency and independence. HAs applying for funds to provide supportive
services must demonstrate that the services will be provided at a higher level than currently provided. Supportive
services may include:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Child care;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Employment training and counseling;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Computer skills training;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

